<subSubSection id="AC92657BFFA3FFC7FF23FCBBFD0C3EEB" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="E43736F0FFA3FFC7FF23FCBBFD0C3EEB" blockId="3.[136,1452,823,955]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="D6FCEAE2FFA3FFC7FF23FCBBFD913E1F" bold="true" box="[189,512,823,847]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">IUCN Red List category:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="23884D73FFA3FFC7FD9EFCBBFC853E1F" box="[512,788,823,847]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Amitostigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kaiyangense">
<emphasis id="D6FCEAE2FFA3FFC7FD9EFCBBFC853E1F" box="[512,788,823,847]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Amitostigma kaiyangense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in an area of less than one square km., only 20 flowering individuals and no more than 100 plants (including seedlings) were seen scattered in mossy places on limestone cliffs along a valley. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="23884D73FFA3FFC7FE7FFCF3FD153EC7" box="[481,644,895,919]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Amitostigma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kaiyangense">
<emphasis id="D6FCEAE2FFA3FFC7FE7FFCF3FD153EC7" box="[481,644,895,919]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">A. kaiyangense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assessed here as Endangered (EN) according to IUCN Red List Criteria (less than 250 mature individuals), (
<bibRefCitation id="80194B01FFA3FFC7FD96FC2FFD033EEB" author="IUCN &amp; IUCN Red List Categories" box="[520,658,931,955]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" refId="ref1464" refString="IUCN. (2001) IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria Version 3.1. Prepared by the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland, and Cambridge, United Kingdom." type="book" year="2001">IUCN, 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
